1
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:04,000
What if we could grow human organs on tiny chips?

2
00:00:04,000 --> 00:00:09,600
Organs on chips mimic human organs, allowing scientists to study diseases and test drugs.

3
00:00:09,600 --> 00:00:13,200
Imagine testing new medicines without risking real patients' lives.

4
00:00:13,200 --> 00:00:18,000
Research shows these chips can predict human responses better than animal models.

5
00:00:18,000 --> 00:00:19,200
But there’s uncertainty.

6
00:00:19,200 --> 00:00:22,400
Not all organs can be replicated accurately yet.

7
00:00:22,400 --> 00:00:22,800
Why?

8
00:00:22,800 --> 00:00:28,000
Advancements in materials and technology could change that, opening doors to personalized medicine.

9
00:00:28,000 --> 00:00:30,000
Curious about more science breakthroughs?

10
00:00:30,000 --> 00:00:31,600
Follow for more insights!
